Crockpot Bolognese

4 oz pancetta, chopped (or center cut bacon)
1 tbsp butter (or olive oil)
1 large white onion, minced
2 celery stalks (3/4c) minced
2 medium carrots (3/4c) minced
2 lbs 95% lean ground beef
1/4 c white wine
2x28oz cans crushed tomatoes
3 bay leaves
salt and fresh pepper
1/4 c chopped fresh parsley
1/2 c half & halft cream

In a large deep saute pan, saute pancetta on low heat until the fat melts, ~4-5 min. Add butter, onions, celery, and carrots, and cook on medium low until soft, ~5min. Increase flame to medium high; add meat, season with salt and pepper and saute until browned. Drain the fat, then add wine; cook until it reduces down, ~3-4min. Add to crock pot. Add tomatoes, bay leaves, salt, and pepper; cover and set to low 6 hrs. After the 6hrs, adjust salt and pepper to taste, add half & half and parsley; stir and serve over your favorite pasta.


Nutrition:
serving size: 1/2 c
Calories: 143
Total fat: 7g
Saturated fat: 3g
Monounsaturated fat: 3g
Cholesterol: 48mg
Sodium 145mg
Carbohydrate: 5g
Dietary fiber: 1g
Sugar: 3g
Protein: 15g
Potassium: 452mg
Iron: 10%
Vitamin A: 30%
Vitamin C: 20%
Calcium: 2%

